Results.ReviewText: As a household of non coffee drinkers it may be a bit strange for me to be writing a review, but this is the coffee I have always had in for guests (probably because it was the coffee my mother always had) and they have always appreciated it.  I also buy for the office in bulk and even have to buy to ship to USA when my boss's wife visits her twin sister.  I like the look of  the new jar, but went for the new refill pack this time, save the planet and all that.
Results.Title: smart new jar

ClientResponses.Response:
Thank you for getting in touch with the NESCAFÉ Gold team. We’re always wanting to improve the product for our loyal fans! After receiving feedback, we've added micro ground coffee to our blend, to give it a richer aroma whilst maintaining the same smoothness. This is also what you can see at the bottom of your cup!

It's sad to hear you're not enjoying the new recipe but we really appreciate you letting us know!

Results.ReviewText:
My wife and I have enjoyed Gold Blend for as long as we can remember. Each morning we take it in turn to make the delicious first cup of the day to drink in bed before we get up. We even take a small jar on holidays as it is a great start to the day. 

How have you managed to destroy an iconic brand ? It now tastes awful - no longer smooth but bitter, and there is a peculiar sludge in the bottom of the finished cup. One of the joys of instant coffee is that it is smooth all the way to the bottom of the cup so you dont have to leave a few mm at the bottom to avoid the nasty brown sludge. The new formulation should never have been offered under the brand name "Gold Blend" .  It is totally misleading to loyal customers who have now purchased rubbish instead of the usual high quality drink. Over the years we must have spent hundreds if not thousand of £ on your product - but no more. 

Sadly you also changed the jar. Although not as iconic as the glass coca cola bottle the gentle curve of the Gold Blend jar was easy to spot on the shelves unlike the drab new version that looks like all the others in the aisle.

Please relaunch your latest idea under a new brand name and give us back the "Gold Blend Classic" in its curved jar.
Results.Title: Gold Blend - an iconic brand destroyed

Results.ReviewText: I really enjoy a coffee made with Nescafe Gold Blend, as I find it mellow and smooth.  It has no bitter aftertaste like so many coffee brands.  I have a few cups of coffee at home each day, and sometimes I buy from a coffee shop.  But I never enjoy shop bought coffee as much as I enjoy my home-made ones, using boiling water, Gold Blend and a dash of cold milk.  I also use this instant coffee when I make a coffee and walnut cake, and the flavour is fabulous!
Results.Title: My Coffee of Choice

Results.ReviewText: I'm very fussy when it comes to coffee but this definitely meets my very high standards.  I love a good strong coffee and Gold Blend is one of the best I've tasted.  Personally I use 1 and a half teaspoons so I get the strength that I like.  The blend is also smooth and does not leave a bitter aftertaste.  Compared to other brands on the market I feel that Nescafe Gold Blend is reasonably priced and good value for money considering how long the jar lasts.
Results.Title: So smooth

ClientResponses.Response: Hi John, during the recent recipe change, micro ground coffee was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee! It's a shame you don't enjoy the changes we've made. We'll be making a note of your feedback.

Results.ReviewText: Nescafe have made a mistake with this. The granules do not dissolve as well as the old version and leaves a stain at the bottom of the mug.  The taste is not as smooth as the older version either.  Coca Cola tried to change their formulations and it didn't work.  Can you bring back the old Nescafe Gold?  Even as another brand like "Classic"?  I will not be buying any more and I only thought the jar had changed.  Does anyone want 5 unopened 200g jars???
Results.Title: Bring back the old Nescafe Gold Blend

Results.ReviewText: While I do enjoy real barista style coffee when I am out and about in cafes, at home I do not want to go to the effort or expense of buying and using the correct equipment for "real coffee". At home, I always use Gold Blend as it literally takes seconds to make and all I need is a mug and a spoon to stir. I add a splash of milk and I am good to go. It tastes pretty good too with a rich coffee aroma that is tasty morning, afternoon or after dinner.
Results.Title: Quick and easy

Results.ReviewText:
Thought I'd try this especially as it was a sample. I'm fussy about my coffee but I was instantly impressed with the outside labelling. Gold, neat and definitely stylish. Looks a quality jar so you'd expect to pay a little more than shops own just to have this jar on your shelf!
Tasting was equally as impressive. I like a good strong cup and hate wishy-washy coffees which have little taste. Instantly, the aroma of warm coffee beans filled the kitchen and permeated all around and I noticed my eagerness to taste. As I poured hot water in, I noticed the grounds dissolved quickly (no floaters) and the taste was superb! Smooth, rich and no bitterness and that impressed me!  I thoroughly enjoyed drinking it so much, I couldn't wait for it to cool down and the aroma lingered whilst I was drinking actively encouraging my taste buds to continue!
Results.Title: Classy Style

Results.ReviewText: I always buy Nescafe Gold coffee however during my monthly shop there was only Nescafe Gold black on the shelf. I thought there wouldn't be much difference and so bought 2 jars. Oh how glad I am. The quality is up to your usual high standard, the taste is absolutely out of this world and is really good value for money. I usually use either full cream milk or a coffee whitener as these enhance the flavour even more. Thank you for a great product.
Results.Title: Great Taste

Results.ReviewText: Having always had Nescafe Gold, its easy to get used to a good thing. Made unemployed a year ago, cutbacks had to be made to my shopping list and cheaper brands bought. Didin't take me long to realise that the cheaper brands were the equivalent of substituting 'real coffee' for soil !!. The rich taste, smoothness and pure taste of Nescafe Gold Blend, means I don't compromise & would rather cut back/miss  something else than my Nescafe coffee.
Results.Title: A 'Must for my Cup'

ClientResponses.Response: It's disappointing to hear you no longer enjoy NESCAFÉ Gold Blend but thank you for sharing your thoughts with us. Occasionally we make changes to the size of our products, driven by a number of factors, including anything from a product reformulation, a change in packaging, or changes to ingredients costs. We'll be making a note of your feedback & passing it to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText:
After drinking nothing but Gold Blend for 25 years, it is time to move to a new brand. Your new recipe is awful, has no aroma when jar opened and if I wanted Barista dregs when the cup is finished, I would buy a Barista brand.

Also sneakily downsized the refill packs, but left the price unchanged.

For the last 25 years, I would always have recommended Gold Blend with a score of 10 - not any more. PLEASE CAN WE HAVE THE ORIGINAL BACK!
Results.Title: If it ain't broke, don't fix it

Results.ReviewText:
Nescafe Gold has been my favorite for years now and I was so pleased to see that it's now in such beautiful packaging - sleek elegant shape and brushed gold - made me smile and think to write to you to congratulate on the idea. I do hope you're going to do Xmas special gift boxes or something with similar design golden cups in them.... please please please please please do :)
In the meantime, Merry Christmas to all of you xxxxx
Margaret
Results.Title: Absolutely Beautiful New Design

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks for getting in touch & letting us know! It's sad to hear you're not liking the changes but we appreciate your feedback.

Results.ReviewText: I have bought this coffee for as long as I can remember but I will now need to seek a different brand. The residue that is now swirling around the bottom of the cup makes me nauseous. It tastes the same but I just cannot deal with the residue. Please, please return to the original recipe, there was nothing wrong with it which makes me think you are including something like ash to bulk out the coffee so you can put less in the jar!
Results.Title: Residue Is Awful

ClientResponses.Response: We’re always wanting to improve the product for our loyal fans (NAME)! After receiving feedback, we've added roast and ground coffee to our blend, to give it a richer aroma whilst maintaining the same smoothness. Watch this video to learn more: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aTUCiAvWyLg&index=22&list=PLBwKOSzTG9BZFv1nKqh8ZxxTOwJaeDaT

Results.ReviewText: I am very disappointed with the new taste and dark scum residue that we now get with Gold Blend, I have drank this coffee for as long as I can remember, certainly 25 years, and one of the previously satisfying elements was the taste and the fact you could drain the cup. If I wanted a residue, I might as well make a coffee using real beans. VERY disappointing, if this is not resolved soon, I will have to choose alternative product
Results.Title: Changed Taste

ClientResponses.Response: We really appreciate everyone taking the time to get in touch with us & leaving their thoughts on the recent changes we've made. All comments are being noted & passed to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText: where do we go from here ??? like many other reviewers my husband and I totally agree with all comments against the awful dregs left in the bottom  of your mug and the bitter taste . why has someone decided to mess with the already perfect taste of a fab instant coffee i do not understand . now have the task of finding nice replacement because gold blend just is not worth boiling the kettle for anymore!!! sad !
Results.Title: wrong wrong wrong !!!!

Results.ReviewText: At 73 I am particular about my coffee, and at one time would only use fresh ground coffee. Then I discovered Nescafe Gold Blend....  it's so good that it tastes like ground coffee, and so popular that other brands, especially own label brands, have named their coffee "gold blend". Well,  they do say that imitation is the sincerest form of flattery! Just make sure when you buy it says NESCAFE gold blend or you'll be disappointed.
Results.Title: The name other brands have copied

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks very much for getting in touch! It's disappointing to hear you're not happy with the changes we've made recently but we really value your feedback & will be letting the wider team know!

Results.ReviewText:
Like so many other reviewers here I've been a life-long Nescafe drinker, Gold Blend was a newer development for me some 20 years ago or so and I have enjoyed the smooth blend every since drinking nothing else but water, but the newer formula is really poor as a development, sooner it has gone back 20 years.
Might as well dust off the old cafetiere for a cup of bitter and residue of beans. Unfortunately you have lost a customer.
Results.Title: What on earth have you done!

ClientResponses.Response: Hey, we’ve recently added roast and ground coffee ground 10 times finer to our new blend of NESCAFÉ Gold Blend. Find out more by watching this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aTUCiAvWyLg&index=22&list=PLBwKOSzTG9BZFv1nKqh8ZxxTOwJaeDaT

Results.ReviewText: I am so upset. I have drank Gold Blend coffee all my life and am devastated to find the recipe has been changed! WHY? Gold Blend is an instant coffee. Instant coffee doesn't have grouts in the bottom like ground coffee. This new Gold Blend has grouts. The flavour has changed too, from a very smooth full flavour to a much weaker flavour. It's is now just very medioca cup of coffee. For me, it is now quite unpleasant to drink.
Results.Title: Nothing like the original

ClientResponses.Response: It's really sad to hear this but thanks for taking the time & letting us know your thoughts! We've made a note of your comments & have passed them for the rest of the team to see.

Results.ReviewText:
Like many other reviewers I too have bought Nescafé Gold Blend for many years despite it not being the cheapest instant coffee. However, I am now switching to another brand as the new recipe is disgusting. The residue at the end of the drink does not shout Barista Expresso, just bitter sludge. If I wanted Barista Expresso there are many more pleasing products on the shelves to select.
I’m sorry but you have lost my custom.
Results.Title: Disappointed with changes

Results.ReviewText: Have been using Nescafe Gold for years after trying many other competitor brands. Nescafe Gold has all the satisfying taste of freshly brewed coffee with the convenience of an instant blend. I find it always tastes better when the mug or cup is warmed slightly before adding the coffee and hot (not boiling) water.  Nescafe Gold compares favourably on price with other premium brands and as such is very good value for money.
Results.Title: Tastes As Good As Fresh Brewed Coffee

Results.ReviewText: I’ve been drinking Gold Blend for many years, was happy to pay more for good coffee. I could see the new packaging but didn’t realise the coffee had changed until I made it. The coffee is weaker, but also seems to sink to the bottom, like a filter coffee, at first I blamed by husband for not stirring it, but I was wrong, even after vigorous stirring it still sinks to the bottom.  I may have to look for a stronger coffee.
Results.Title: Not as good as it was

Results.ReviewText:
I have been a fan of  Gold Blend Instant  for many years and  enjoy several black coffees a day  (my only other drink is water).

Since the packaging has changed I feel the standed of coffee has to, when  I reach 
the end of my drink it tastes very gritty this has happened over several jars.
In the past I would have given a  5 star rating

I am not the only one to notice several friends agree 
What has happened ?
Results.Title: What has happened

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thank you very much for getting in touch! We really appreciate your comments & we are certainly passing them on to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText: After drinking Gold Blend for years now I have found the new coffee awful, this has led me to search on the internet and find this forum. I don't want barista style grains left in the bottom of my cup, if I wanted those I assume I could get them by buying Gold Barista instead of Gold Blend. I bought Gold Blend instead of Gold Barista because I don't want non soluble micro ground coffee in my cup. The aroma when opening a new jar is no longer there. Why advise other reviewers to change coffee if they don't like micro ground coffee, why not just leave a good product alone. I will be changing to another coffee, all I can suggest is that if you eventually listen to your customers and change the coffee back to its former glory that you make a big song and dance about it as soon a lot of people will be left not drinking it and will not know that you have changed it back.
Results.Title: Terrible changes have ruined this coffee

Results.ReviewText: This is my go to blend of coffee, and has been for the past 30 plus years.  The taste is mellow rich and so distinctive,  I have tried your impersonators, but no one can match the taste my Gold Blend gives me.  From the first cup in the morning, I know this is the perfect start to my day.  I drink it in the office, to keep me going, then switch to your decaff version for the second half of the day.  The perfect coffee.
Results.Title: Cannot be beaten

Results.ReviewText:
I love to have a cup of good coffee and this is it - NESCAFE GOLD BLEND
I hate early mornings because I am moody and not properly woken up. Lovely cup of coffee makes all much easier.
Great taste and very satisfying. Opening the jar and you get a wonderful aroma of ground coffee, even thought this is an instant coffee. It isn't  a strong, overwhelming smell but it certainly does gives you a sudden hit of aroma. 
The granules are normal size but the colour is much lighter.
The aroma doesn't disappear when you add the granules to your cup. 
Nescafe is one of the best coffee in the world and very easy to make and as the name suggests " Gold Blend", means coffee beans are of the highest quality.
I am very loyal to this brand because once you taste something great to love it even more. 
I would recommend a coffee- lover to try this brand and discover amazing taste.
Results.Title: Coffee Time

Results.ReviewText: I tried This product about three months ago . Now normally a jar of  instant coffee lasts me ages as I like to have ground (Proper coffee as I call it ). I was pleasantly surprised at the quality and smooth taste. I think you have converted me from a proper coffee drinker to an instant drinker.Just to prove this fact I had to but another jar after 3 weeks. A big thanks to Nescafe, can't wait to try the other blends.
Results.Title: A little cup of heaven

ClientResponses.Response: Hey, we're disappointed to hear this but we really value your feedback. If you don’t like the rich taste or the micro ground coffee you could try NESCAFÉ Gold Crema. This has a similar taste to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend but it's smoother and doesn't contain micro ground coffee.

Results.ReviewText: We’ve been big coffee drinkers for many years & have always considered Nestle Gold Blend to be the “gold standard” for instant coffee, sadly the reformulation in our view just doesn’t work, the rounded flavour has disappeared having been replaced by bitter notes along with insoluble residues left in the base of the cup. Please, please do let me know which Nestle coffee is the closest match to the original formation?
Results.Title: A big disappointment

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks very much for letting us know your thoughts on the new recipe. We really appreciate your feedback! The residue you can see at the bottom of your cup is micro ground coffee that was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend during the recent change. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee!

Results.ReviewText: We have always been so very pleased with Nescafe Gold Blend..but now find it dreadful. It is quite bitter with a 'chemical' aftertaste..and we certainly fear drinking to the bottom of the mug as there is always a residue of brown sludge. We can make a good jug of coffee with ground coffee beans if we fancy it ..but so enjoyed the previous recipe Gold blend...a mug of comfort & delight no longer available it seems.
Results.Title: Bitter with brown sludge on the bottom of mug :(

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, it's disappointing to hear you're not a fan of the changes we've made but thank you very much for letting us know!

Results.ReviewText: My wife and I are on our 2nd jar of the new Gold Blend but we don't like. The taste or flavour is nothing like the old brew. I used to kick start my day with a heaped spoon full now I have to put in atleast two to anything close to the taste and flavour of the old brew. Plus I.m certainly not prepared to pay seven pound fifty for something that used to sell at around four to five quid yours ex Nescafe Gold drinker
Results.Title: Not liked

Results.ReviewText: I tried this after drinking Nescafé original for years and now I'm hooked it's the perfect blend of rich and smooth that I can make a strong cup to wake me up in the morning and a slightly less strong one the rest of the day with the same great taste. a number of family members and friends  have tried it when visited and all liked it and several have converted Well done Nescafé for getting this blend so perfect
Results.Title: Perfect blend

Results.ReviewText: I have been drinking Nescafé Gold Blend for years always enjoyed the taste and smell particularly when you opened a new jar. What has happened? Bought a new jar, opened expecting the usual aroma, the smell was different, better :) Drinking the first cup of the 'new' jar was even more pleasant. The taste was better, it left a Nescafe taste in my mouth:) I enjoy Nescafé coffees, the Gold Blend being my favorite.
Results.Title: What has Nescafé done to my favourite coffee?
